The Issue: Unusual traffic spikes detected on the law office network.
The Solution: Using Tcpdump to capture and inspect packet data.
# Melissa Rachel Wozney - Network Lab
# Objective: Capture 100 packets on the 'eth0' interface to inspect for ICMP flooding.
Network-Traffic-Analysis.md
sudo tcpdump -i eth0 -c 100 -v

# Findings: Identified a high volume of 'ping' requests from a single external IP.
# Action: Configured firewall rule to drop traffic from the suspicious source.
